Borussia Dortmund continued their spectacular implosion this season, losing 2-1 at struggling Werder Bremen. 

It was their 10th defeat in 17 league games sending them into the winter break in 17th place, just a point off the bottom.

Talented teenager Davie Selke scored Werder's first goal in the third minute and last season's Bundesliga runners-up never recovered, their leaking defence and lack of attacking ideas proving costly.

