Werder hit them on the break with Selke charging down the right wing past two Dortmund players to deliver a cross for Fin Bartels on the hour.

Mats Hummels' diving header in the 69th gave the visitors hope and Shinji Kagawa should have done better when he fired over the bar from 11 metres as Dortmund pressed for an equaliser.

The result left Dortmund, champions in 2011 and 2012, on 15 points, two behind VfB Stuttgart who are in the relegation play-off spot. Freiburg, last with 14 points, could send Dortmund bottom if they beat Hannover on Sunday.

